            "question": "What is the difference between a website and a funnel?",
            "answer": "A website gives visitors many paths to explore. A funnel is built around one focused outcome, such as booking a call, requesting a quote, downloading a guide or joining a campaign. Both matter, but funnels are designed for measurable conversion."
          },
          {
            "question": "Can a funnel connect to CRM, email and SMS?",
            "answer": "Yes. That is the point. A lead should not sit in an inbox. Funnel activity can feed the CRM, trigger email and SMS follow-up, create tasks, segment contacts and help your team see which campaigns are producing real opportunities."
          },
          {
            "question": "Can we build different funnels for different services?",
            "answer": "Yes. A builder might need quote funnels for renovations, booking funnels for consultations, and reactivation funnels for old enquiries. A coach might need webinar, course and application funnels. The structure should match the offer."
          },
          {
            "question": "Do we need every feature on day one?",
            "answer": "No. The best approach is to launch a clear first version, measure the result, then improve it. The page has been written to show where the platform can go as your funnel tools expand."
          }
